\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Length amplification ratio $\mathbb {E}[A^2 \mid L_{\max }] / \mathbb {E}[A^2 \mid L_{\min }]$. Ratios $\gg 1$ indicate that long trajectories dominate the gradient (GRPO); ratios $\ll 1$ indicate precision-optimal suppression. Column-wise best (lowest ratio) is bolded. Under short-range dependence, $\Delta L$ ($\alpha {=}1$) achieves the lowest ratio; under compound symmetry, LV-CAPO adapts to the superlinear variance law and dominates.\relax }}{55}{table.caption.25}%
